The Hillman Companies, Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 24, 2017 12:09 AM ET
Trading Companies and Distributors

Company Overview of The Hillman Companies, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
The Hillman Companies, Inc., together with its subsidiaries, provides hardware-related products and related merchandising services to retail markets. The company markets and distributes approximately 114,000 stock keeping units (SKUs) of hardware items. Its fasteners product line encompasses standard and specialty nuts, bolts, washers, screws, anchors, and picture hanging items, as well as a line of indoor and outdoor project fasteners for use with drywall and deck construction. The company also designs and manufactures keys, key accessories, and code cutter units; designs, manufactures, and assembles the engraving equipment; offers individual and/or packaged letters, numbers, signs, safety ...
The Hillman Companies, Inc., together with its subsidiaries, provides hardware-related products and related merchandising services to retail markets. The company markets and distributes approximately 114,000 stock keeping units (SKUs) of hardware items. Its fasteners product line encompasses standard and specialty nuts, bolts, washers, screws, anchors, and picture hanging items, as well as a line of indoor and outdoor project fasteners for use with drywall and deck construction. The company also designs and manufactures keys, key accessories, and code cutter units; designs, manufactures, and assembles the engraving equipment; offers individual and/or packaged letters, numbers, signs, safety related products, driveway markers, and various sign accessories, such as sign frames; and provides metal shapes and threaded rod products. In addition, it markets the builder’s hardware products, including various common household items, such as coat hooks, door stops, hinges, gate latches, hasps, and decorative hardware under the Hardware Essentials brand. The company sells its products to hardware stores, home centers, mass merchants, pet supply stores, and other retail outlets principally in the United States, Canada, Mexico, Australia, Latin America, and the Caribbean. The company was founded in 1964 and is headquartered in Cincinnati, Ohio.
Detailed Description


