The Hillman Companies, Inc. Key Developments

Hillman Companies, Inc. Announces the Resignation of Jeffrey S. Leonard as Chief Financial Officer, Executive Vice President of Finance, and Treasurer of Hillman, Effective August 11, 2017
Jul 21 17
The Hillman Companies, Inc. announced the resignation of Jeffrey S. Leonard as Chief Financial Officer, Executive Vice President of Finance, and Treasurer of Hillman, agreed that, effective August 11, 2017. Mr. Leonard would resign from his positions with Hillman and affiliated entities to allow him to pursue other opportunities that are geographically closer to his family and residence in Florida.


Hillman Companies Inc. Declares Trust Preferred Securities Distribution, Payable on July 31, 2017
Jul 12 17
President and chief executive officer Gregory Gluchowski of the Hillman Companies Inc. reported a cash distribution of USD 0.241667 on the company's trust preferred security. The distribution will be paid on July 31, 2017 to shareholders of record date as of July 21, 2017.


The Hillman Companies, Inc., Q1 2017 Earnings Call, May 16, 2017
May 8 17
The Hillman Companies, Inc., Q1 2017 Earnings Call, May 16, 2017


