The Hillman Group, Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg










































  





















































































July 24, 2017 12:09 AM ET
Trading Companies and Distributors

Company Overview of The Hillman Group, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
The Hillman Group, Inc. markets, packages, and distributes hardware-related products and merchandising services to retail markets in North America. The company offers fasteners, including nuts, bolts, washers, screws, anchors, and picture hanging items; zinc, chrome, and galvanized plated steel fasteners; stainless steel, brass, and nylon fasteners; and indoor and outdoor project fasteners for use in drywall and deck construction. It also provides keys, key duplication systems, and key accessories; code cutter units; and individual and/or packaged letters, numbers, signs, safety related products, and driveway markers, as well as sign accessories, such as sign frames. In addition, the company...
The Hillman Group, Inc. markets, packages, and distributes hardware-related products and merchandising services to retail markets in North America. The company offers fasteners, including nuts, bolts, washers, screws, anchors, and picture hanging items; zinc, chrome, and galvanized plated steel fasteners; stainless steel, brass, and nylon fasteners; and indoor and outdoor project fasteners for use in drywall and deck construction. It also provides keys, key duplication systems, and key accessories; code cutter units; and individual and/or packaged letters, numbers, signs, safety related products, and driveway markers, as well as sign accessories, such as sign frames. In addition, the company offers Quick-Tag, a patented, consumer-operated vending system that engraves and dispenses pet identification tags, military style I.D. tags, holiday ornaments, and luggage tags; FIDO system; and TagWorks engraving system, a proprietary laser system that allows consumers to watch the engraving process. Further, it supplies threaded rod products, such as hot and cold rolled rods, and weld-able and plated products, as well as all-thread rods in galvanized steel, stainless steel, and brass; and provides household items, such as coat hooks, door stops, hinges, gate latches, hasps, and decorative hardware. The Hillman Group, Inc. sells its products to hardware stores, home centers, mass merchants, pet supply stores, and other retail outlets principally in the United States, Canada, Mexico, Australia, Latin America, and the Caribbean. Its customers include Walmart, HomeDepot, Lowe’s, Sears, Tractor Supply, PetSmart, Grainger, Menards, and PETCO. The company was founded in 1964 and is based in Cincinnati, Ohio. The Hillman Group, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of The Hillman Companies, Inc.
Detailed Description


10590 Hamilton AvenueCincinnati, OH 45231United StatesFounded in 1964



