The Hillman Group, Inc. Key Developments

Hillman Group, Inc.  Announces the Resignation of Jeffrey S. Leonard as Chief Financial Officer, Executive Vice President of Finance, and Treasurer of Hillman, Effective August 11, 2017
Jul 21 17
The Hillman Group, Inc. announced the resignation of Jeffrey S. Leonard as Chief Financial Officer, Executive Vice President of Finance, and Treasurer of Hillman, agreed that, effective August 11, 2017. Mr. Leonard would resign from his positions with Hillman and affiliated entities to allow him to pursue other opportunities that are geographically closer to his family and residence in Florida.


The Hillman Companies, Inc. and The Hillman Group, Inc. Announce Management Appointments
Feb 9 17
The Hillman Companies, Inc. and The Hillman Group, Inc. announced two new members of its Executive Team. Effective immediately, Kim Corbitt joins Hillman as Chief Human Resources Officer, while Zach Sherburne joins as Chief Information Officer. In her new role as Chief Human Resources Officer, Corbitt will have global leadership responsibility for all Human Resource functions for The Hillman Group.  In this role she will lead talent development processes, compensation, benefits, employee relations, recruiting, and organizational culture development.  Before coming to the Hillman Group, Corbitt served as Sr. Human Resource Leader at Procter & Gamble. Chief Information Officer, Zach Sherburne, will have leadership responsibility for all information technology capabilities at Hillman.  Sherburne has an extensive background in information systems management, having served most recently as Sr. VP & Chief Information Officer at Nextgen Healthcare. Prior to that, Zach served as the CIO for the Hardware and Home Improvement Division of Stanley Black & Decker and Spectrum Brands.


Ajustco Expands North American Distribution Via Partnership with Hillman
Oct 26 15
Ajustco announced an exclusive distribution agreement with the Hillman Companies, Inc. and The Hillman Group, Inc. (collectively, Hillman) for its AjustLock line of innovative, adjustable barrel bolts and slide bolts. AjustLock launched in 2013, as Ajustco's product, and has since been recognized with industry awards for both product and packaging innovation.


